// Terminal WebSocket Server
// Bridges WebSocket connections to tmux sessions using Bun's native PTY support.

Each WebSocket connection spawns a tmux attach-session process with a PTY terminal.
Active connections are tracked in a module-level Map keyed by WebSocket instance.
Terminal output is forwarded to the WebSocket; WebSocket input is forwarded to the PTY.

FUNCTION parseMessage(data) -> TerminalMessage | null
  Parse the incoming data as JSON.
  IF it has type='resize' with numeric cols and rows, return a ResizeMessage.
  IF it has type='data' with a string data field, return a DataMessage.
  IF JSON parsing fails, treat the raw text as a DataMessage.
  Return null for unrecognized structured messages.

---

FUNCTION handleTerminalConnection(ws, tmuxSession) -> void                              EXPORT
  CALLS: parseMessage (terminal-ws-server), handleTerminalDisconnection (terminal-ws-server)
  Detect the tmux binary path (checking /opt/homebrew/bin/tmux, /usr/local/bin/tmux, /usr/bin/tmux).
  Ensure the target tmux session exists (create detached if not), enable mouse mode.
  Capture up to 10,000 lines of scrollback history and send to the WebSocket before attaching.
  Spawn tmux attach-session with TERM=xterm-256color via Bun's PTY terminal option.
  The PTY data callback forwards terminal output to the WebSocket.
  The PTY exit callback logs the exit.
  Store the process, terminal, and tmuxSession in the activeTerminals map.
  Register a process.exited handler to close the WebSocket and clean up the map entry.
  On any spawn error, send an ANSI-red error message to the WebSocket and close it.

---

FUNCTION handleTerminalMessage(ws, message) -> void                                     EXPORT
  CALLS: parseMessage (terminal-ws-server)
  Look up the active terminal for the WebSocket; warn and return if not found.
  Parse the message. IF resize, call terminal.resize(cols, rows). IF data, call terminal.write(data).
  Errors are logged but not fatal.

---

FUNCTION handleTerminalDisconnection(ws) -> void                                        EXPORT
  Look up and remove the active terminal for the WebSocket.
  IF found, close the PTY terminal and kill the process.

---

FUNCTION getActiveTerminalCount() -> number                                             EXPORT
  Return the number of currently active terminal connections.
